// Cross-module generic free-fn dispatch.
//
// Calls a generic free function defined in `genericlib` via the
// module-qualified form (e.g. `genericlib.identity(x)`). The checker
// infers the type arguments from the receiver/argument types and
// records them in the `call_type_args` side table; codegen consumes
// the table here in `generateModuleMethodCall` to monomorphize.
//
// Three call sites with `int` arguments exercise the specialise-cache
// dedup path (one specialised symbol must be reused, not three). One
// call with `f64` arguments proves a different inferred type yields a
// distinct specialised symbol. A call to `pick_first` covers a
// multi-type-param generic.
import genericlib;

fn main() {
    println(genericlib.identity(1));
    println(genericlib.identity(2));
    println(genericlib.identity(3));
    println(genericlib.identity(3.5));
    println(genericlib.pick_first(42, 9.9));
}
